      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in Ebedmelech, the Cushite, or Ethiopian, of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 38:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", we have instances of the presence of such slaves in the royal households. The history of every ancient nation shews the universality of the traffic. Of these slaves each great household had two classes: (1) those “bought with money,” men of other races, captives in war, often, probably, (",
